OL,3,CWarning issued after fire caused by
OL,4,Cdisposable vapes in lorry
OL,6,FResearch by the National Fire Chiefs
OL,7,FCouncil (NFCC) and Recycle Your
OL,8,FElectricals has found that the number
OL,9,Fof battery fires in bin lorries and at
OL,10,Fwaste sites in the UK has reached an
OL,11,Fall-time high, with an increase of 71%
OL,12,Ffrom 700 in 2022 to more than 1,200 in
OL,13,Fthe last year.
OL,15,FA statement from MAWWFRS said: "With
OL,16,Fan increase in the number of portable
OL,17,Felectrical items containing lithium-
OL,18,Fion batteries, there comes a
OL,19,Fsignificant fire risk if they are
OL,20,Fbinned instead of being recycled.
